The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Moga, Aug. 3 (PTI): Six persons of Bhinderkalan village lost their vision after eye operations at a local hospital, officials said.          
	They were operated on at Guru Ramdass Charitable Trust Hospital on July 16 and lost their vision after they developed an eye infection, said Dr Tajinder Gupta, assistant civil surgeon, who conducted the preliminary enquiry.                  
	 Pune (PTI): The Shiv Sena has drafted in McDonalds to sponsor a convention of shiv vadapav vendors in Mumbai, party mouthpiece Saamna said on Sunday. Party officials said Uddhav Thackeray had taken the initiative to popularise the Maharashtrian snack at international level.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A Nashik-based CBSE school has offered to adopt the son of the soldier killed in last weeks firing along the LoC. This is our humble tribute to Ajit Gaokars supreme sacrifice. The school will take care of his sons education, boarding and all related expenses, authorities said.                  
	 Jaipur (PTI): A terror suspect who had taken shelter in a mosque has been arrested in Sajjangarh. Ijufar Rehman, 53, a resident of Bharauch in Gujarat, was trying to flee from a village after arousing suspicion that he was a terrorist.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A former employee of a private company, who was sacked in 1977, has been paid the salary for the 14 months remaining in his contract under Delhi High Court orders. Avineshwar Sawhneys petition said the company sacked him on the ground that it had lost confidence in him.                   
	 Chennai (PTI): A partial lunar eclipse will occur on August 17 and will be visible in the country from 1.06 to 4.14am, Tamil Nadu Science and Technology Centre executive director Iyyam Perumal said. Another partial lunar eclipse will occur on February 9, 2009. The last total lunar eclipse had occurred on February 21, 2008.                                                                                                                          
